The paper deals with a communication system involving multiple antennas and transmission of multiple data streams, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of limited feedback for channel knowledge and quantization techniques suggest a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of random quantization, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and the comparison of different feedback schemes, which falls under Multimedia (cs.MM).
